1. Make a Character Blueprint
2. Make a Game Instance Blueprint
3. Make a Game State Blueprint
4. Make a Player Controller Blueprint
5. Make a HUD Blueprint
6. Make a GameMode Blueprint and change the classes to the things I just made.
7. In Maps & Modes in Project Settings  chage the gamemode, instance class






------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Mouse Control in game
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. In input in project settings, make a MouseX and MouseY Axis input.
2. Go to PlayerControllerBlueprint
3. for InputAxis MouseX, link it with add yaw input
4. for inputAxis MouseY, link it with add pitch input


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Movement Input
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. In input in project settings, make a MoveForward and MoveRight Axis input.
2. Go to Character Blueprint
3. make a Moveforward and moveright input axis
4. link them to add movement input
5. for world direction in add movement input, make a get control rotation, break rotator, get the z(yaw) and link it to make rotator
6. from there, link it to get forward vector and link it to add movement input linked to moveforward
7. from make rotator, link it to get right vector and link it to add movement input linked to moveright.


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Jump Action
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Make a Jump action in project settings
2. go to Character blueprint
3. make a Jump inputaction and link the pressed to jump function that is already made.
4. link the released in jump input action to stop jumping function.



------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Making a Material for my Arm Mesh
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Make a Material
2. Get a Texture that ends with _D and connect it with Texture Sample and link it to Base Color
3. Same with Metalic but this ends with _M
4. same with Normal but this ends with _N
5. make a value by pressing 1 and clicking, link it to roughness and give it as I want(.25) in this lecture



------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Adding Arms to Character
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. add a camera in Character Blueprint and check use pawn control rotation to true
2. make the camera be where my head is
3. make a Skeletal Mesh as a child of Camera
4. link the arm mesh I made to the skeletal mesh in details
5. in animation mode in animation change it to use animation asset and find rifle idle
6. check out use controller rotation yaw and check out cast shadow
